1
00:00:10,750 --> 00:00:15,166
[SAYA exhales]

2
00:00:15,666 --> 00:00:18,125
So, uh, listen Coconuts.

3
00:00:18,208 --> 00:00:19,500
Yeah?

4
00:00:19,583 --> 00:00:20,875
[SAYA] There's something
I've been wanting to ask you

5
00:00:20,958 --> 00:00:22,250
for a while now.

6
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,833
[KOKONOTSU]
What's up, Saya?

7
00:00:23,916 --> 00:00:25,041
[SAYA]
You may not have noticed,

8
00:00:25,125 --> 00:00:27,291
on the account that
you're kinda oblivious,

9
00:00:27,375 --> 00:00:29,708
but this has been bothering me.

10
00:00:29,791 --> 00:00:32,833
You need to be honest here.

11
00:00:32,916 --> 00:00:34,041
[SAYA sighs]

12
00:00:34,125 --> 00:00:35,875
[KOKONOTSU gasps]

13
00:00:35,958 --> 00:00:41,625
[SAYA] Why... is your shop...
so... run down looking?

14
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:48,375
[KOKONOTSU] It's been
three months since then.

15
00:00:49,666 --> 00:00:54,625
♪


16
00:02:28,666 --> 00:02:29,833
[KOKONOTSU gasps]

17
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:31,125
[BOYS]
Hm?

18
00:02:33,791 --> 00:02:36,625
Kokonotsu! It's all
up to you now!

19
00:02:36,708 --> 00:02:39,791
[YO laughs]
Yippie!

20
00:02:39,875 --> 00:02:43,291
[KOKONOTSU]
Damn you, Yo!

21
00:02:44,708 --> 00:02:49,083
[KOKONOTSU] Ugh. I feel
like eating some good food.

22
00:02:49,166 --> 00:02:54,750
Hm. Curry, sushi, or <i>tonkatsu</i> .

23
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:57,500
[KOKONOTSU gasps]
Jeez for a second there,

24
00:02:57,583 --> 00:03:00,041
I feel like I said something
that would summon Hotaru.

25
00:03:00,125 --> 00:03:03,750
Summon, like a weird ritual.

26
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:04,500
[tires screech]

27
00:03:04,583 --> 00:03:06,166
Hold on a second.

28
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,458
[KOKONOTSU]
Whoa. Hotaru?!

29
00:03:15,541 --> 00:03:17,875
Thanks for wait...ing.

30
00:03:17,958 --> 00:03:22,958
[groans]

31
00:03:23,041 --> 00:03:25,958
You said it... Kokonotsu!

32
00:03:26,041 --> 00:03:27,041
[KOKONOTSU]
Don't try to act cool

33
00:03:27,125 --> 00:03:28,541
when you're obviously
out of breath!

34
00:03:30,666 --> 00:03:33,458
[HOTARU sighs]
That's the stuff!

35
00:03:33,541 --> 00:03:35,958
Ramune after a long run
really hits the spot,

36
00:03:36,041 --> 00:03:37,250
know what I'm talkin' about?

37
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:39,125
Why did you run
all the way here?

38
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:40,625
[HOTARU giggles]

39
00:03:40,708 --> 00:03:42,583
[KOKONOTSU gasps]

40
00:03:42,666 --> 00:03:45,791
[HOTARU]
The time has finally come...!

41
00:03:45,875 --> 00:03:48,750
I've thought about making it
"today's theme" so many times,

42
00:03:48,833 --> 00:03:50,708
but then I'd think, "Maybe this
isn't the right time,"

43
00:03:50,791 --> 00:03:52,666
so I've restrained myself.

44
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:54,666
But the fateful day has arrived,

45
00:03:54,750 --> 00:03:57,166
and since you used the
sacred summoning ritual,

46
00:03:57,250 --> 00:04:02,041
I present to you the legend
among deep-fried <i>dagashi</i> !

47
00:04:02,125 --> 00:04:03,708
It's Big Katsu!

48
00:04:03,791 --> 00:04:06,000
Uh, big what now? <i>Katsu</i> ?

49
00:04:06,083 --> 00:04:07,833
[gasps]

50
00:04:07,916 --> 00:04:09,625
[KOKONOTSU] So, " <i>tonkatsu</i> " is
the magic word to summon her?

51
00:04:09,708 --> 00:04:11,916
Yeah, I've been waiting
for the word " <i>tonkatsu</i> "

52
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,500
to roll off your
lips forever.

53
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:15,375
Couldn't you just
ask me to say it?

54
00:04:15,458 --> 00:04:17,916
Anyway!

55
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,041
Well, as you may be aware,

56
00:04:20,125 --> 00:04:22,958
combining <i>dagashi</i> with
rice is kind of my thing.

57
00:04:23,041 --> 00:04:25,333
Uh, is that supposed
to be embarrassing?

58
00:04:25,416 --> 00:04:27,708
Also, did you bring
your own rice bowl?

59
00:04:27,791 --> 00:04:29,916
So, what's the deal
with Big Katsu?

60
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,333
Like what makes it special?

61
00:04:32,416 --> 00:04:35,416
Big Katsu. <i>Tonkatsu</i> .

62
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:38,083
Hotaru?

63
00:04:38,166 --> 00:04:41,833
So I could be wrong, but Big
Katsu isn't pork. It's fish.

64
00:04:41,916 --> 00:04:43,500
[KOKONOTSU grunts]

65
00:04:43,583 --> 00:04:46,125
Duh, it's in <i>tonkatsu</i> style!
How can you not know that?

66
00:04:46,208 --> 00:04:48,833
Uh, okay. That really hurts.

67
00:04:48,916 --> 00:04:50,333
[HOTARU]
I suppose.

68
00:04:50,416 --> 00:04:52,583
In order for you to understand,
I'll have to tell you the

69
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:55,250
top-secret origin
story of Big Katsu.

70
00:04:55,333 --> 00:04:56,791
The origin story?

71
00:04:56,875 --> 00:04:58,500
[HOTARU]
Yes, Kokonotsu, you see,

72
00:04:58,583 --> 00:05:01,291
this story all begins...
with squids!

73
00:05:01,375 --> 00:05:02,708
[KOKONOTSU]
What?!

74
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:04,208
[HOTARU] The company that
created it was developing

75
00:05:04,291 --> 00:05:07,250
a product, and they used
squid as the main ingredient.

76
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:08,625
But they had a rough go of it

77
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:11,000
because they couldn't
find suppliers.

78
00:05:14,416 --> 00:05:15,541
Say what?

79
00:05:15,625 --> 00:05:17,541
But they refused to
give up on their idea!

80
00:05:17,625 --> 00:05:18,791
Since they couldn't get squid,

81
00:05:18,875 --> 00:05:21,208
they decided to go
with fish instead.

82
00:05:21,291 --> 00:05:23,750
They made sheets from fish
and soaked them in a sauce,

83
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:26,791
that's Amatarakko,
sweet dried squid style.

84
00:05:26,875 --> 00:05:30,416
This is Ika Ajiten, it's deep
fried and sauce-less.

85
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:31,750
[KOKONOTSU]
Wait a minute.

86
00:05:31,833 --> 00:05:34,875
They're both totally
amazing and I adore them!

87
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:37,875
And yet, the developers
still weren't satisfied

88
00:05:37,958 --> 00:05:39,833
with their product!
So they asked,

89
00:05:39,916 --> 00:05:43,000
"How can we surpass the
taste of real dried squids?"

90
00:05:43,083 --> 00:05:43,833
[KOKONOTSU]
Huh?

91
00:05:43,916 --> 00:05:45,333
[HOTARU]
What's wrong?

92
00:05:45,416 --> 00:05:47,208
Hold on, they tried to surpass
the taste of dried squids

93
00:05:47,291 --> 00:05:48,500
with fake dried squids?

94
00:05:48,583 --> 00:05:50,541
[HOTARU]
Yes, try to keep up.

95
00:05:50,625 --> 00:05:52,500
Their hardship continued.

96
00:05:52,583 --> 00:05:54,791
Through wind and rain,
they struggled on.

97
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:57,500
Even though they wanted to
collapse from exhaustion,

98
00:05:57,583 --> 00:05:59,041
they never quit.

99
00:06:01,458 --> 00:06:05,000
[HOTARU] All for the sake
to aim for greater heights!

100
00:06:06,375 --> 00:06:08,000
And so...

101
00:06:09,208 --> 00:06:11,458
And so...?

102
00:06:11,541 --> 00:06:13,083
They thought <i>tonkatsu</i>
would be delish,

103
00:06:13,166 --> 00:06:15,416
so sha-bam, that's how
Big Katsu was born.

104
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:18,458
[KOKONOTSU yells]
That's it?

105
00:06:18,541 --> 00:06:21,208
Hold up, you didn't
like the story?

106
00:06:21,291 --> 00:06:22,708
No, I mean, I guess it's fine.

107
00:06:22,791 --> 00:06:24,791
I just thought there would
be a bit more to it.

108
00:06:24,875 --> 00:06:27,083
And besides I wanted
to eat <i>tonkatsu</i> .

109
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:28,500
Oh, wait a second,

110
00:06:28,583 --> 00:06:30,958
are you saying Big Katsu
can't beat <i>tonkatsu</i> ?

111
00:06:31,041 --> 00:06:33,708
You sayin' only squids
can surpass other squids?

112
00:06:33,791 --> 00:06:35,250
No...

113
00:06:35,333 --> 00:06:37,083
[HOTARU] You think all of their
blood, sweat and tears was--

114
00:06:37,166 --> 00:06:39,583
That's not what I said at all!

115
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:42,916
That's not the point! It's not
about winning or losing!

116
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,625
I think not being the
real thing is exactly

117
00:06:44,708 --> 00:06:46,916
what makes those
<i>dagashi</i> so appealing!

118
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,333
Big Katsu is delicious even
when you don't eat it on rice

119
00:06:49,416 --> 00:06:50,708
like a weirdo!

120
00:06:50,791 --> 00:06:52,166
And when you eat Ika Ajiten,
you wouldn't be like,

121
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:55,458
"Man, I prefer real
squid tempura," now would you?

122
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:57,833
Personally, I'm really happy
that Big Katsu was born

123
00:06:57,916 --> 00:07:01,208
as result of their
stupid struggle! Oh...

124
00:07:01,291 --> 00:07:02,458
[KOKONOTSU gasps]

125
00:07:02,541 --> 00:07:05,708
[HOTARU giggles]
Just as I expected.

126
00:07:05,791 --> 00:07:06,958
[KOKONOTSU gasps]

127
00:07:07,041 --> 00:07:08,958
[HOTARU]
You really are a <i>dagashi</i> genius.

128
00:07:09,041 --> 00:07:10,333
[KOKONOTSU]
Huh?

129
00:07:10,416 --> 00:07:11,666
[HOTARU]
A rising star!

130
00:07:11,750 --> 00:07:13,583
The successor of
Shikada Dagashi!

131
00:07:13,666 --> 00:07:14,916
[KOKONOTSU gasps]

132
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:18,041
Great job putting your
talents to good use, yay!

133
00:07:19,375 --> 00:07:22,458
[HOTARU] Soon you'll have a
video blog just like your dad!

134
00:07:22,541 --> 00:07:27,916
Please, Hotaru. I beg of you,
don't bring up his video blog.

135
00:07:29,625 --> 00:07:31,166
[HOTARU]
And so...

136
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:33,375
[SAYA]
Pasta.

137
00:07:33,458 --> 00:07:35,083
[KOKONOTSU, TO]
Huh?

138
00:07:35,166 --> 00:07:37,916
I kinda feel like eating pasta.

139
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,791
Go and whip some up.
It is on our menu.

140
00:07:40,875 --> 00:07:45,000
Good idea. Plus the pasta you
make is pretty tasty, Saya.

141
00:07:45,083 --> 00:07:47,041
Oh. Uh, you think so?

142
00:07:47,125 --> 00:07:49,416
Well, I guess it's true people
in our town are always

143
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:52,333
bragging about how awesome
my pasta tastes, you know?

144
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:53,541
--[TO] Sure.
--[SAYA] Hey!

145
00:07:53,625 --> 00:07:56,208
Anyway, I don't want
our boring old pasta.

146
00:07:56,291 --> 00:07:59,166
I wanna go to one of those
fancy Italian restaurants

147
00:07:59,250 --> 00:08:01,916
with live piano music
and hot waiters!

148
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,500
[TO] Good luck finding
a place like that

149
00:08:03,583 --> 00:08:05,000
in this dump of a town.

150
00:08:05,083 --> 00:08:06,500
[SAYA]
Yeah...

151
00:08:06,583 --> 00:08:09,125
Wait, you want your
big bro to make some?

152
00:08:10,583 --> 00:08:11,166
[SAYA]
Ugh!

153
00:08:11,250 --> 00:08:12,041
What?

154
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:13,041
--[skidding]
--[bells chime]

155
00:08:13,125 --> 00:08:14,083
[ALL]
Huh?

156
00:08:15,458 --> 00:08:18,541
Thanks for waiting!
Looks like you're in a real-

157
00:08:18,625 --> 00:08:23,583
[groans]

158
00:08:25,583 --> 00:08:26,791
Whoa, you okay?

159
00:08:26,875 --> 00:08:28,791
Seriously, I need you to
quit running everywhere

160
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:30,625
just to look cool, Hotaru!

161
00:08:34,375 --> 00:08:36,791
Anyway, you said you
wanted some pasta?

162
00:08:36,875 --> 00:08:38,375
[SAYA gasps]

163
00:08:38,458 --> 00:08:41,041
Yeah! Do you know
a good restaurant?

164
00:08:41,125 --> 00:08:42,666
I shall make it for you!

165
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:45,166
Wait, that's not
what I asked for.

166
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:50,666
[HOTARU] It's being...
summoned...to this place!

167
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:52,708
So, uh, what is this?

168
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:54,666
Ah, you must be surprised.

169
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:58,041
Yes, Master Saya, spaghetti
exists in the <i>dagashi</i> world.

170
00:08:58,125 --> 00:08:59,958
I promise I'm not impressed.

171
00:09:00,041 --> 00:09:03,666
All things considered,
it's not even a unique idea.

172
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:06,791
[TO] Heh. It kinda just
looks like Cup Noodles.

173
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:08,791
Well yeah, this was
originally made

174
00:09:08,875 --> 00:09:10,583
by an instant noodle company.

175
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,541
[HOTARU chuckles]
Yep, he's right.

176
00:09:12,625 --> 00:09:15,333
They used their know-how to
sublimate it into a <i>dagashi</i>

177
00:09:15,416 --> 00:09:17,250
that's as close to the
real thing as possible,

178
00:09:17,333 --> 00:09:18,916
which we're looking at, see?

179
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,458
What now?

180
00:09:20,541 --> 00:09:24,291
[HOTARU] Once three minutes
have passed, drain the water.

181
00:09:24,375 --> 00:09:27,875
Then you mix in half of the soup
powder, like I'm about to do.

182
00:09:29,416 --> 00:09:31,375
[HOTARU]
This is the king of Italian food

183
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:32,833
in the <i>dagashi</i> world!

184
00:09:32,916 --> 00:09:34,666
Peperoncino!

185
00:09:39,041 --> 00:09:40,041
Now, try it!

186
00:09:40,125 --> 00:09:41,875
Uh, okay.

187
00:09:45,166 --> 00:09:47,208
[gasps]
It's delicious!

188
00:09:47,291 --> 00:09:47,958
[KOKONOTSU, TO]
Huzzah!

189
00:09:48,041 --> 00:09:49,333
I know, right?

190
00:09:49,416 --> 00:09:50,958
Kinda strange though.

191
00:09:51,041 --> 00:09:53,708
Because I feel like
I know this flavor.

192
00:09:53,791 --> 00:09:55,333
[gasps]

193
00:09:55,416 --> 00:09:57,833
Wait a second, this is just
salt-flavored <i>yakisoba</i> !

194
00:09:57,916 --> 00:10:00,583
This... This pasta is a lie!

195
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:04,500
Heh! Well, you're observant
as always, Master Saya.

196
00:10:04,583 --> 00:10:08,041
Naturally. Take a
look at this packet.

197
00:10:08,125 --> 00:10:10,625
[SAYA gasps]
Pasta style?

198
00:10:10,708 --> 00:10:15,250
Uh-huh. That's right.
There's also a ramen style.

199
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,833
Allow me to explain.

200
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:18,875
If you put in all the soup
powder without draining

201
00:10:18,958 --> 00:10:20,625
the water, you get ramen!

202
00:10:20,708 --> 00:10:24,166
Hold on, for real? So it
could totally go either way?

203
00:10:24,250 --> 00:10:25,625
Oh, but wait.

204
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:27,208
Does that mean you
just throw out, like,

205
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:29,333
the rest of the powder?

206
00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:32,708
Non, non, it actually
gets better!

207
00:10:32,791 --> 00:10:35,041
Once you're done eating,
put the remaining powder

208
00:10:35,125 --> 00:10:39,208
in the container...
and pour hot water into it.

209
00:10:41,291 --> 00:10:43,958
Voila, you have an
after-dinner soup, bon appetite!

210
00:10:44,041 --> 00:10:47,500
Whoa, no way! That's so awesome!

211
00:10:49,583 --> 00:10:52,583
[SAYA] Surprisingly, I really
enjoyed this pasta.

212
00:10:52,666 --> 00:10:54,375
Thanks so much!

213
00:10:54,458 --> 00:10:57,375
Ottimo! Am I right, Master Saya?

214
00:10:57,458 --> 00:10:58,750
[SAYA]
Say what now?

215
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:00,416
Oh, that's the
superlative form

216
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:02,500
of the Italian
word for delicious.

217
00:11:02,583 --> 00:11:04,791
Everybody say "Ottimo!"

218
00:11:04,875 --> 00:11:05,625
[ALL gasp]

219
00:11:05,708 --> 00:11:07,500
Now, Ottimo!

220
00:11:07,583 --> 00:11:10,250
[ALL]
O-Ottimo.

221
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:12,208
[HOTARU]
With feeling!

222
00:11:12,291 --> 00:11:15,000
[ALL grunt]
Uh, ottimo!

223
00:11:15,083 --> 00:11:16,416
[HOTARU]
One more time!

224
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:20,083
[ALL]
Ottimo!

225
00:11:20,166 --> 00:11:25,125
♪


226
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:20,041
[HOTARU] Next time.

227
00:12:20,125 --> 00:12:23,000
"Baseball Board Game Gum,
Pop Pop Boat, and..."

228
00:12:23,083 --> 00:12:25,083
Bath time with Master Saya!

